{
  "text": "Soil samples collected from agricultural field were milled to break the lumps and sieved. The sieved samples were grinded to make it more homogeneous powderded form. Then 1 g of powdered sample was weighed and transferred into 100 mL beaker. To this 2 mL of water in which 0.5 gram of KOH pellets dissolved were added and the mixture was heated on hot plate until the water evaporates and fuses for 2 min. Then it was diluted up to 50 mL. 5 mL aliquot of diluted sample solution was used to determine As by following the procedure given as above [CITATION_1] .",
